---
/**
 * CaseDivider.astro — dotted horizontal divider between case sections.
 * Figma asset: Assets/Images/Case Lucida/divider.svg
 *
 * Pattern (same as the Header menu-tab-border, see CLAUDE.md decision #16):
 *   - Inline SVG with stroke-dasharray="0.1 8" → renders as round dots 8px apart
 *   - vector-effect="non-scaling-stroke" → stroke-width stays 2px under any scale
 *   - preserveAspectRatio="none" → SVG stretches horizontally to container width
 *
 * Reference copy preserved at src/assets/icons/case-divider.svg.
 *
 * The parent flex container (`.case__content` with `gap: 48px`) provides the
 * 48px breathing room above and below the divider.
 */
---

<svg
  class="case-divider"
  preserveAspectRatio="none"
  viewBox="0 0 870 2"
  height="2"
  fill="none"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
  aria-hidden="true"
  focusable="false"
>
  <path
    d="M1 1H869"
    stroke="#BBBBBB"
    stroke-width="2"
    stroke-linecap="round"
    stroke-dasharray="0.1 8"
    vector-effect="non-scaling-stroke"
  />
</svg>

<style>
  .case-divider {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 2px;
    /* overflow:visible so round-cap dots (2px diameter) aren't clipped by the
       2px-tall SVG box. Otherwise dots render as flat ticks instead of circles. */
    overflow: visible;
    /* The dots' visual gap stays 8px regardless of stretch thanks to
       vector-effect=non-scaling-stroke + preserveAspectRatio=none above. */
  }
</style>
